{"title":"- Hemorrágia digestiva alta-2024","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/- Hemorrágia digestiva alta-2024.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Hemorragia\\NDigestiva Alta","guid":"dO2ldAOSsiUJQYoKCGUo4A","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Introducción","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Definición: Sangrado originado entre el esfínter esofágico superior y la flexura duodeno-yeyunal (ángulo de Treitz).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Incidencia: 40-150 casos por 100,000 habitantes.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"4","parent":"0","text":"Causas\\NComunes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"5","parent":"4","text":"1. Úlceras gastroduodenales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"• Responsable de hasta un tercio de los casos.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"4","text":"2. Erosiones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"4","text":"3. Várices esófago-gástricas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"4","text":"4. Síndrome de Mallory Weiss","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Desgarro mucoso-submucoso distal a la unión gastroesofágica, provocado por un aumento brusco de la presión intraabdominal (emesis).","guid":"PXLyEU8ppmFnj_qgPvo_dA","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"4","text":"5. Causas esporádicas: Múltiples otras causas con menor frecuencia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"4","text":"6. Causa no identificable: Hasta en un 20% de los pacientes tras una primera endoscopia.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"0","text":"Clasificación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"• No variceal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"15","parent":"14","text":"• Mortalidad: 2%-10%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"14","text":"• Evolución: Autolimitado (80%)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"14","text":"• Endoscopia: Urgente, dentro de 12 a 24 h del diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"18","parent":"14","text":"• Uso de Inhibidores de Bomba de Protones: Altas dosis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"14","text":"• Vasoactivos: No requerido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"14","text":"• Antibióticos: No requerido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"14","text":"• Terapia Endoscópica: Solo en sangrado activo o alto riesgo de resangrado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"13","text":"• Variceal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"• Mortalidad: 20%-40%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"• Evolución: Recidivante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"22","text":"• Endoscopia: Antes de 12 h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"22","text":"• Uso de Inhibidores de Bomba de Protones: No recomendado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"22","text":"• Vasoactivos: Previos a endoscopia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"22","text":"• Antibióticos: Al ingreso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"22","text":"• Terapia Endoscópica: Siempre","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"Mortalidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"• Disminución: Desarrollo de unidades de pacientes críticos y terapias farmacológicas específicas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"32","parent":"30","text":"• Mayor mortalidad en hemorragia variceal: Riesgo elevado de daño hepático agudo sobre crónico, sobreinfecciones bacterianas, disfunción de otros órganos.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"0","text":"Evaluación\\NInicial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"Anamnesis\\NCompleta","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"• Tiempo de evolución","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"• Cuantía de pérdidas hemáticas","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"• Síntomas asociados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"34","text":"• Episodios previos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"34","text":"• Comorbilidades","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"34","text":"• Uso de medicamentos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"41","parent":"40","text":"• AINEs, antiagregantes, anticoagulantes, hierro oral.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"42","parent":"34","text":"• Síntomas de sangrado mayor:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"• Lipotimia, ortostatismo, síncope, oliguria, palpitaciones.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"34","text":"• Compromiso hemodinámico o anemia severa:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• Confusión, agitación, compromiso de conciencia.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"33","text":"Examen\\NFísico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"• Hemodinamia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"• Presión arterial, frecuencia cardíaca.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"47","text":"• Perfusión clínica","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"• Estado de conciencia","guid":"CQ_Be1BHnaZsClQFHmRjeQ","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"46","text":"• Signos de daño hepático crónico y coagulopatía:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"52","parent":"51","text":"• Equimosis, petequias, otros.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"53","parent":"46","text":"• Examen de tacto rectal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"54","parent":"53","text":"• Características de las deposiciones.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"33","text":"Exámenes de\\NLaboratorio","guid":"","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"• Hemograma completo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"55","text":"• Grupo sanguíneo/Rh","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"55","text":"• Pruebas de coagulación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"55","text":"• Perfil hepático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"55","text":"• Función renal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"55","text":"• Lactato","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"55","text":"• Riesgo cardiovascular:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"• Enzimas cardíacas, electrocardiograma.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"64","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico\\NDiferencial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"65","parent":"64","text":"• Descartar:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"• Epistaxis posterior, hemoptisis.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"67","parent":"64","text":"Determinar Origen del\\NSangrado Digestivo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"• Hemorragia digestiva\\Nalta vs. baja:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"• Melena: Puede presentarse en hemorragia baja de colon derecho.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"• Hematoquecia con compromiso hemodinámico: Sugiere hemorragia digestiva alta.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"67","text":"• Manejo como sangrado de origen alto en caso de duda.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"64","text":"Etiología Variceal\\Nvs. No Variceal","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"• Anamnesis y examen físico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"72","text":"• Laboratorio:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"75","parent":"74","text":"• Trombocitopenia, alteración de aminotransferasas (GOT/GPT) sugiere sangrado variceal.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"72","text":"• Hipertensión\\Nportal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"• 85% etiología variceal, 15% no variceal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"• Tratamiento inicial como variceal hasta verificación endoscópica.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"79","parent":"0","text":"Estratificación del Riesgo de\\NResangrado y Mortalidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"• Determinantes:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"• Etiología del sangrado, comorbilidades, compromiso hemodinámico, disfunción de órganos.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"82","parent":"79","text":"• Hematemesis:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"• Generalmente implica hemorragia mayor (> 500 ml).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"84","parent":"79","text":"• Sangrado variceal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"• Evaluar funcionalidad hepática (escala de MELD).","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"0","text":"Manejo\\NGeneral","guid":"","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Monitorización y\\NReanimación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"88","parent":"87","text":"• Monitorización hemodinámica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"87","text":"• Reanimación\\Nprecoz con fluidos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"• Dos vías venosas periféricas gruesas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"• Administrar cristaloides según metas hemodinámicas.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"87","text":"• Intubación\\Norotraqueal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"• Hematemesis severa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"• Compromiso de conciencia.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"92","text":"• Comorbilidad justificante.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"96","parent":"86","text":"Hemoglobina y\\NTransfusión","guid":"","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"• Hemoglobina precoz: No confiable en las primeras horas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"• Reanimación guiada por respuesta hemodinámica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"• Manejo transfusional\\Nrestrictivo:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"• Administración de glóbulos rojos en Hb < 7 g/dl.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"101","parent":"99","text":"• En patología cardiovascular, Hb < 9 g/dl.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"102","parent":"86","text":"Procinéticos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"103","parent":"102","text":"• Eritromicina 250 mg IV: Previo a la endoscopia, mejora visualización de la mucosa y reduce necesidad de repetir el examen.","guid":"EsG_xiszcblf-PrAYxLDag","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"86","text":"Ácido\\NTranexámico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"• No recomendado: No muestra beneficio en sangrado digestivo, puede aumentar\\Nriesgo de convulsiones, trombosis venosa profunda y tromboembolismo pulmonar.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"106","parent":"86","text":"Sonda\\NNasogástrica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"• No recomendada rutinariamente: No útil para vaciamiento gástrico,\\Nrara vez justificada para definir origen alto del sangrado.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"86","text":"Momento del Procedimiento\\NEndoscópico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"• Realización: Cuando el paciente esté reanimado y hemodinámicamente estable.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"• Hemorragia\\Nno variceal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"111","parent":"110","text":"• Endoscopia urgente: 12-24 h del diagnóstico.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"110","text":"• Endoscopia antes de 4 h: Resultados desfavorables\\N(reanimación incompleta, sobretratamiento endoscópico).","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"0","text":"Estratificación\\Ndel Riesgo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"• Escala de\\NGlasgow-Blatchford:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"• Predice riesgo de resangrado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"116","parent":"114","text":"• Parámetros clínicos: PAS > 110 mmHg, melena, síncope, insuficiencia cardíaca/hepática.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"114","text":"• Parámetros de laboratorio: Nitrógeno ureico, hemoglobina.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"114","text":"• Determina necesidad de hospitalización y estudio endoscópico urgente.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"119","parent":"113","text":"• Escala de\\NRockall","guid":"","children":[{"id":"120","parent":"119","text":"• Determina riesgo de mortalidad.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"119","text":"• Parámetros clínicos preendoscópicos y hallazgos endoscópicos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"119","text":"Parámetros\\NPuntuación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"Edad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"124","parent":"123","text":"60-79 años 1","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"123","text":"≥ 80 años 2","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"122","text":"Frecuencia cardíaca","guid":"","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"> 100 latidos/min 1","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"122","text":"Presión arterial sistólica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"< 100 mmHg 1","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"130","parent":"122","text":"Comorbilidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"131","parent":"130","text":"Cardiopatía coronaria 2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"130","text":"Insuficiencia renal, hepática, otra patología mayor o cáncer metastásico 3","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"122","text":"Diagnóstico endoscópico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Úlcera péptica, patología erosiva o esofagitis (no Mallory-Weiss) 2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"Cáncer en tracto gastrointestinal alto 3","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"122","text":"Estigma de sangrado","guid":"","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"Sangre, sangrado activo, vaso visible o coágulo 2","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"119","text":"• Puntaje","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"< 2: Manejo ambulatorio.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"> 6: Alto riesgo de mortalidad.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"141","parent":"0","text":"Manejo\\NEspecífico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"Uso de Inhibidores de\\NBomba de Protones (IBP)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"143","parent":"142","text":"• Omeprazol IV:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"144","parent":"143","text":"• Bolo inicial 80 mg.","guid":"Jkq_QUkBkr1mTfAZUrbtiQ","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"143","text":"• Dosis de mantenimiento: Continua (8 mg/h)\\No intermitente (40-80 mg/12 h).","guid":"ffa2Llu-8oRjcCHITfUz-Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"142","text":"• Mejora sobrevida, disminuye resangrado y necesidad de terapia endoscópica.","guid":"Age_RE-n5SBXtrwGH6Q5UQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"141","text":"Manejo de\\NAnticoagulantes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"• Suspender y revertir efectos: No retrasar inicio del estudio endoscópico.","guid":"KrgoolioB5kFIJeOH6XOFw","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"• Reinicio: A partir de los 7 días desde la detención del sangrado (antes en alto riesgo cardiovascular).","guid":"XDq5vw5iIZkoCvb3Ga2r0A","children":[]}]},{"id":"150","parent":"141","text":"Endoscopia\\NDigestiva Alta","guid":"","children":[{"id":"151","parent":"150","text":"• Finalidad: Diagnóstica y terapéutica.","guid":"XYvH-g-a8ZdYp-tEZpuJdQ","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"150","text":"• Beneficios: Reduce necesidad de transfusión, resolución quirúrgica y mortalidad.","guid":"X-KPPUSyP0kE_-zvcqRPAw","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"150","text":"Clasificación de\\NForrest","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"Ia Hemorragia arterial pulsátil","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"Ib Hemorragia napa o goteo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"IIa Vaso visible en el fondo de la úlcera","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"157","parent":"153","text":"IIb Coágulo adherido a la base de úlcera","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"158","parent":"153","text":"IIc Base cubierta de hematina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"153","text":"III Úlcera sin estigmas de hemorragia","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"160","parent":"150","text":"• Terapia endoscópica para sangrado activo o\\Nalto riesgo de resangrado (Forrest Ia a IIb).","guid":"","children":[{"id":"161","parent":"160","text":"Métodos de Hemostasia\\NEndoscópica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"Inyectoterapia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"Solución salina, epinefrina, esclerosantes (alcohol, monoetanolamina, polidocanol),\\Ntrombina (con o sin fibrina), cianoacrilato","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"164","parent":"161","text":"Electrocoagulación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"165","parent":"164","text":"De contacto: Sondas mono o bipolares","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"164","text":"Sin contacto: Coagulación de argón plasma, láser Nd-YAG","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"167","parent":"161","text":"Mecánicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"168","parent":"167","text":"Clips hemostáticos, ligaduras","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"169","parent":"161","text":"Tópicos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"170","parent":"169","text":"Polvos hemostáticos","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"171","parent":"160","text":"Helicobacter\\Npylori","guid":"","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"• Test de ureasa: Controversial, baja sensibilidad en presencia de sangre y por acción de IBP.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"171","text":"• Biopsias para descartar neoplasias: Realizar de forma diferida, tras control del sangrado.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"174","parent":"141","text":"Control Endoscópico\\NPrecoz","guid":"","children":[{"id":"175","parent":"174","text":"• No recomendado rutinariamente.","guid":"b-WxA2T4569VtxJuFjBwRA","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"174","text":"• Indicado en:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"• Alto riesgo de resangrado.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"• Terapia endoscópica insatisfactoria.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"• Mala visualización de la mucosa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"176","text":"• Resangrado.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"141","text":"Reinicio de Alimentación","guid":"","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"• Oral: Líquidos claros tras endoscopia.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"183","parent":"141","text":"Hemodinamia Inestable","guid":"","children":[{"id":"184","parent":"183","text":"• Considerar manejo por radiología intervencional o cirugía.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"183","text":"• Tomografía computada con fase arterial (Angio-TAC): Información topográfica para radiólogo o cirujano.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"186","parent":"141","text":"Post-Endoscopia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"187","parent":"186","text":"• Alto riesgo de resangrado: IBP IV y hospitalización por 72 h.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"186","text":"• Bajo riesgo de resangrado: IBP IV por 24 h, luego IBP oral en doble dosis\\N(4-6 semanas úlcera duodenal, 6-8 semanas úlcera gástrica).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"189","parent":"141","text":"Pacientes con AINEs/Ácido Acetilsalicílico","guid":"F8P1C0xXf5Z55mSTGcu0Tw","children":[{"id":"190","parent":"189","text":"• Evaluar suspensión.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"189","text":"• Asociar IBP permanentemente si no es posible suspenderlos.","guid":"Lfp6bDwFAodo513OK_Ewmg","children":[]}]},{"id":"192","parent":"141","text":"Estudio Endoscópico\\NNegativo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"193","parent":"192","text":"• Repetir examen: Antes de diagnosticar hemorragia digestiva de probable origen intestinal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"192","text":"• Buscar lesiones tipo Camerón o aneurisma cirsoideo de Dieulafoi.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"195","parent":"0","text":"Hemorragia Digestiva Alta Variceal:\\NManejo Específico","guid":"G_9ktlGdIJo5b-2gRreNWQ","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"Hospitalización y Monitorización","guid":"","children":[{"id":"197","parent":"196","text":"• Unidades de pacientes críticos: Monitorización continua y tratamientos específicos.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"195","text":"Vasopresores","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"• Fundamental en el manejo: Disminuyen la hipertensión portal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"• Eficacia: Detienen el sangrado digestivo en ~80% de los pacientes, previenen resangrado precoz.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"198","text":"• Inicio: Previo al estudio endoscópico, desde la sospecha diagnóstica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"198","text":"• Elección: Terlipresina (disminuye mortalidad, fácil administración, baja incidencia de efectos adversos).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"198","text":"Vasopresores en Hemorragia\\Npor Várices y Dosis Habituales","guid":"","children":[{"id":"204","parent":"203","text":"Terlipresina Previo al control del sangrado: 2 mg IV cada 4-6 h; Posterior al control del sangrado: 1 mg IV cada 4-6 h 2-5 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"203","text":"Octeotride Bolo 50 mcg IV seguido de infusión 50 mcg/h 2-5 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"206","parent":"203","text":"Somatostatina Bolo 250 mcg IV seguido de infusión 250-500 mcg/h 2-5 días","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"203","text":"Vasopresina 0,2-0,4 U/min IV 24 h","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"208","parent":"195","text":"Betabloqueo\\NNo Selectivo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"209","parent":"208","text":"• No recomendado en fase aguda: Bloquea la acción de catecolaminas, impidiendo mecanismos de compensación hemodinámica.","guid":"KkUoMz6QhS9mXVtwBn_h8g","children":[]}]},{"id":"210","parent":"195","text":"Antibióticos","guid":"TPKmyA5oUmcgLY3CKn5uwg","children":[{"id":"211","parent":"210","text":"• Cefalosporinas de 3ra generación o quinolonas: Durante 7 días, asociados a disminución de mortalidad.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"212","parent":"195","text":"Terapia\\NEndoscópica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"• Várices esofágicas: Ligaduras con bandas elásticas.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"212","text":"• Várices gástricas: Escleroterapia con cianocrilato.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"212","text":"• Erradicación variceal endoscópica: Completar en forma diferida.","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"216","parent":"195","text":"Procedimientos\\Nde Rescate","guid":"","children":[{"id":"217","parent":"216","text":"• Indicaciones: Sangrado variceal no controlado con vasopresores y endoscopia terapéutica.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"218","parent":"216","text":"• Opciones:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"• Sonda de balones Sengstaken-Blakemore.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"220","parent":"218","text":"• Prótesis autoexpansible cubierta.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"218","text":"• TIPS (transyugular intrahepatic\\Nportosystemic shunt):","guid":"","children":[{"id":"222","parent":"221","text":"• Disminuye hipertensión portal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"223","parent":"221","text":"• Control de hemorragia y prevención de resangrados.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"221","text":"• Limitaciones: Poco disponible, elevado costo, alta incidencia de complicaciones (encefalopatía, disfunción hepática, otros).","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"225","parent":"218","text":"• Endocoils: Opcional para el manejo de várices gástricas en centros avanzados.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]}]},"node_count":225,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"- Hemorrágia digestiva alta-2024","id":"map_680","resolved_references":[]}